node.text: Bears’ GM Ryan Pace told reporters that his team will continue to start Andy Dalton and be patient with rookie first-round pick Justin Fields. “I just feel like we're just in a good position with Andy. It starts with how we feel about Andy, and we're very confident in him and where he's at. So, there's no need for us to rush Justin….Playing quarterback in the NFL, there's so much that goes into that and so much different than you'd even see in the preseason -- the weekly preparation, seeing NFL defenses in the regular season and all those things. I just think the more time he has to learn that and observe that, the better off for him."
